    "narrative": "For the Zurich Zebras on this April 12th slate, the lineup is optimized to maximize stolen base efficiency and capitalize on favorable SP matchups. **Christian Yelich** (72.61) and **Trea Turner** (71.43) anchor the squad today as our premier starts. **Christian Yelich** draws a massive boost from a dynamic platoon advantage (13%) against Littell, while **Trea Turner** leverages his leadoff spot and a neutral matchup against Gallen to drive our highest baseline projection. Further down the order, **Kyle Schwarber** (67.82) and **Colt Keith** (67.49) are high-confidence plays; **Colt Keith** specifically benefits from an opponent with a slow delivery, adding a vital 2% cushion to his SB probability, while **Kyle Schwarber** continues to provide elite xwOBA stability despite the tough Gallen pairing.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Jerar Encarnacion** (56.19) on the bench. While his park factors are excellent, his suboptimal #8 batting position creates a ceiling that simply could not displace our starters, who carry better lineup protection. Similarly, **Victor Scott II** (55.66) was considered for his speed profile, but the lower projected efficiency compared to the rest of the outfield meant he remains in reserve. We are monitoring the situation with **Yordan Alvarez** (55.60) closely; his lineup is currently pending, and he faces the toughest test of the day against Gilbert. Should **Yordan Alvarez** drop lower than the assumed #2 spot, his already suppressed score\u2014weighted heavily by a -19% SP skill penalty\u2014may put his status for future starts under review. The presence of wind in specific venues provides a subtle tailwind for **Caleb Durbin**, **Chase Meidroth**, and **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, ensuring they remain strong, active participants in today\u2019s rotation.",
